erational and ethical dimensions of academic publishing, with Publishers acting as key implementers of these regulatory frameworks.\",49\r\n358,AI POLICY,DE GRUYTER BRILL,De Gruyter Brill has developed an AI policy to guide authors on the responsible and secure use of AI in research,49\r\n368,AI POLICY,EMERALD,Emerald has developed an AI policy to govern the use of AI technologies in academic publishing,49\r\n372,AI POLICY,TAYLOR & FRANCIS,\"Taylor & Francis has developed an AI policy to guide the ethical and responsible use of Generative AI tools in academic publishing, providing comprehensive guidance on how these technologies should be integrated into scholarly communication. This policy reflects the organization's commitment to ensuring that the application of AI in academic publishing adheres to high ethical standards and supports the integrity of research output. The AI policy serves as a framework for authors, editors, and publishers to navigate the evolving landscape of artificial intelligence in academia.\",49\r\n275,INTEGRITY,AI POLICY,\"The AI policy framework is designed to uphold the integrity of research and academic publishing. These policies aim to ensure the integrity of research by imposing restrictions on the use of AI tools in content creation and data reporting. Additionally, AI policies are structured to support the maintenance of research integrity, particularly in contexts where artificial intelligence is involved, thereby reinforcing ethical standards and accountability within the academic ecosystem.\",49\r\n342,CONFIDENTIALITY,AI POLICY,\"The AI policy, which includes confidentiality as a core principle, emphasizes the importance of maintaining data privacy and protecting proprietary information when using AI tools. Specifically, Elsevier's AI policy underscores the need for confidentiality throughout the publication process, particularly when employing AI technologies. This policy also addresses the risks to confidentiality posed by Genera